            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-08 11:40:29" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to break an object into two or more parts (in the NT κλάω and κλάσις are used exclusively for breaking bread)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to break</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to break bread</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages important distinctions are made for terms meaning ‘to break’ depending on the substance involved. For example, the breaking of a stick or a bone would require quite a different term from that used in speaking of breaking bread. Furthermore, the action of breaking bread would probably imply breaking into several pieces rather than a single break. Such a distinction may likewise require a special term.</Comments>
